## Usage Guidelines

### Do's ✅
- Use PRIMARY for main actions and brand elements
- Use SUCCESS for positive metrics and confirmations
- Use WARNING for cautionary information
- Use ERROR for critical issues and errors
- Maintain high contrast for readability
- Use neutral colors for backgrounds and text

### Don'ts ❌
- Don't use bright, saturated colors (not professional)
- Don't use too many colors at once
- Don't use low contrast combinations
- Don't use red/green only to convey information (colorblind users)
- Don't override the medical aesthetic with playful colors

